6.Brief the difference between Class and Struct. Also, provide some information on when to use them.

Class:

	A  class in c++ can be defined as a collection of related variables and functions encapsulated in a single structure
Keyword:class
Usage:generally used for large amount of data

Structure:
	A structure can be referred to as a user defined data type possessing its own operations.
Keyword:struct
Purpose:generally grouping of data,and used amount of data.
	
